Indonesia will host a summit on January 6 to address the aftermath of Asia's natural disaster.
The conference will include 23 countries and focus on earthquake and tsunami relief efforts.
Japan has deployed emergency workers to affected areas, with a significant aid effort directed towards Sumatra.
Various countries, including China and Uzbekistan, have sent humanitarian aid to Indonesia.
Australia pledged a historic $1 billion in loans and grants for reconstruction.
Japan also committed to long-term support for Aceh and North Sumatra.
Bangladesh is providing relief goods, including high-energy biscuits, to tsunami victims in Indonesia and Sri Lanka.
